      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Community Action Opioid Response Act of 2018</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Office of Community Services within the Department of Health and Human Services to establish a grant program that helps low-income individuals, families, and communities affected by the national opioid epidemic. Grants must be awarded to Community Action Agencies (local organizations that work to reduce poverty in low-income communities) for specified activities relating to opioid misuse and abuse, including education, outreach, prevention, and treatment services. </p>]]></text>
